description:
FULL RECIPE BELOW. Vegan Pinoy Curry. This is my sister’s specialty and I’m so happy that she was generous enough to let us know her technique! I made it vegan and did some tweaks. Overall, I’m delighted with the results. Thank you ate! 🥰

INGREDIENTS:
3 1/2 cups coconut milk (about 2 cans)
1 pound tofu, torn into big chunks
1/4 - 1/2 cup cornstarch for coating
Cooking oil
4-6 cloves of garlic, peeled. crushed, and minced
2 yellow onions, peeled and chopped
1 small red bell pepper, deseeded and chopped
1 small green bell pepper, deseeded and chopped
1 medium carrot, peeled and chopped
2 medium yukon potatoes, peeled and chopped
liberal dash of sea salt
2 tablespoons curry powder, or more to taste
Mushroom seasoning (optional)

Note:
I prefer to have big chunks of tofu to look similar to chicken curry, but you're more than welcome to also just cut in cubes.

DIRECTIONS:
In a pot, cook the coconut milk for 15 minutes over low heat or until slightly reduced and thicker.

In a bowl, combine the cornstarch and tofu. Mix well to coat.

Heat a medium pan over medium heat and pour enough cooking oil to cover the bottom of the pan. Once the oil is hot, fry the tofu.

Lower the heat and add the garlic, onions, and bell peppers. Mix well.

Mix in the carrots and potatoes.

Season with salt and curry powder. Mix well and cook for 1-3 minutes or until the onions have turned soft and translucent.

Pour the reduced coconut milk and mix well. Cover the pan and let it cook over low heat for 15 minutes, occasionally mix to make sure nothing sticks on the bottom of the pan.

Check if the potatoes are done by piercing them with a fork. If they're still hard, cook for another 3 minutes or until soft enough to pierce. Adjust seasoning to taste. You can also add mushroom seasoning (optional).

Turn off the heat and serve hot with rice.
